Alice Chapin https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alice_Chapin 0 Alice Chapin or Alice Ferris (August 28, 1857 – July 5, 1934) was an American who became an actress, playwright and suffragette in England. She returned to America and played roles in silent films.
